1. Purpose

This license is designed for the seed stage of the CoCivium / CoSuite project.
It prioritises safety, integrity, and trust, and is intentionally more protective
than typical open source licenses. The authors intend to relax these terms and
transition suitable parts of the work to more open licensing once governance,
legal, and safety structures are mature.

2. Definitions

"Software" means the source code, documentation, configuration files, diagrams,
and any other files in this repository and its derivative works.

"You" means the individual or entity exercising permissions under this license.

3. Grant of rights

Subject to the conditions in this license, You are granted a non-exclusive,
non-transferable, revocable license to:

- use and run the Software for your own internal evaluation;
- read and study the Software to understand its design and behaviour;
- contribute improvements back to the CoCivium / CoSuite ecosystem, for example
  through patches, pull requests, or advisory notes.

No other rights are granted. In particular:

- You may not redistribute the Software, in whole or in part, in source or
  compiled form, to any third party, except with prior written permission from
  the steward entity designated for this repository.
- You may not offer the Software as a hosted service or integrate it into
  commercial products or services, except with prior written permission.
- You may not remove or alter any copyright, license, or attribution notices.

