  contact@InSeed.com

9. Future evolution and opening

The intent of the CoCivium project is that, as safety and governance structures
mature, suitable parts of the Software will be made available under more open
licenses that allow broader reuse by humanity.

Nothing in this license obliges the authors to make this change, but the
commitment to evolve toward a safe and open ecosystem is part of the moral
frame of the project.

10. Termination

This license terminates automatically if You breach any of its terms.
Upon termination You must stop using the Software and destroy any copies in
your possession, except to the extent you are required to retain them by law.

The authors may choose to offer You a new license under different terms. Such a
license must be in writing and will supersede this license for the scope it
covers.

